<br>
This is the art of Area Effects Nuking.<br>
<br>
Some of you are familiar w/the Quad Kiting Raptors.  The only similarity here is that your going to be doing something new, and that it involves AOE spells.<br>
<br>
It is possible to clear Fear 10 mobs at a time if you use these tactics.  It is quite awesome to run into fear w/4 groups.  To have the chanter AE stun garbage, and to have the other casters AE nuke the garbage.  Bing Zone broken.  Some of you can recall multiple corpse retrievals and failed attempts at breaking fear.  Hellish nights spent not hoping for a rez, but just to get your gear back and camp.<br>
<br>
PBAOE avoids all sorts of issues.  Now secondly, PBAOE is VERY good exp.  If your killing 10 monsters at a time, and get 10 &quot;You have gained EXP&quot; messages on one screen, your a very happy camper.  I've only personally had 6 EXP messages on one screen, but I was never put in the WIZ groups.<br>
<br>
Now for the reason I'm telling you about this.<br>
<br>
PBAOE will save us hours of CR, and Hours of time getting to the King and Queen.  You know how long it takes to pull one mob at a time and kill it.  What if we all kill 10 mobs at a time, three times.  Then we rest for 5 or 10 minutes and do it again.  How fast do you think we are going to get to King?<br>
<br>
1.  This promotes quick in an out attacks on chardok.<br>
2.  This promotes flawless plane raids.<br>
3.  This promotes a new tactic that is just fun as hell.<br>
<br>
Now for the basics.<br>
<br>
1.  You group tightly the casters.<br>
2.  The tanks sit out of their view.<br>
3.  A heavy tank pulls the mobs, and keeps them in a cluster, not a single file line.  He brings them right over the top of the casters.<br>
4.  The chanter AE Stuns, non stop.<br>
5.  The Wizards, Mages, Clerics, Druids, etc AE Nuke.<br>
6.  The tanks play cleanup on any mobs that miss the AE nukes.<br>
7.  This is VERY graphics intensive.  The tanks MUST stay out of the way until called in for clean up.  This reverses the normal roll of the tanks and the casters.  Those tanks who are all pumped up to run in and kill something, are gonna be having fits.  Some will feel useless.  Just remind them you need them, this is just a tactic to get a job done.<br>
<br>
I welcome all comments, and thoughts.  I really feel we as a guild should practice this a lot.  I think we should schedule a night in chardok to just do PBAOE tactics.  I have tried this in KC before, and the people in zone constantly got trained.  This is why I suggest Chardok, a normally untouched zone, with plenty of mobs for everyone.<br>
<br>
Kikulle<br>
<br>
