<br>
Don't confuse PBAOE with AOE, most classes have AOE.  The only difference between PBAOE and AOE is that PBAOE hit unlimited number of mobs while AOE only kill 4 at time.  With multiple group, AOE is fine but just one group, PBAOE is important spell.<br>
<br>
In sebilis, from my past experience, here is an example: a group of 4 wizards, chanter and a paladin.  (yes, no cleric, rarely need cleric) because this group know what to do.  We cleaned from B3 toward Pickler/Brogg and back and forth.  The highest mob kills in one wave is 22 mobs near Brogg area.  Was very hairy but made it.<br>
<br>
If doing on krups, we always run out of mana.  It is better doing mobs with less hp, the quicker death for them.<br>
<br>
This tactic don't work Howling Stones cuz of harm touch <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Jyll's Static Pulse, a 53rd PBAOE stun mobs too so we wizards stun and hurt the mobs while the enchanter chain stun the mobs.  And we rarely get hit <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also in Hole, a group of a magician, shaman, 2 wizards, cleric and warrior clean up Hole pretty much but the golems sometime resist stuns so one of us get almost beated up badly.<br>
<br>
If two group doing this tactic, can clean up the whole zone in a breeze since can clean up about 30 mobs at one wave with 2 enchanters chain stun mobs.<br>
<br>
Any class with AOE could clean up room quick.<br>
<br>
It is very useful spell if doing raid or rapid experience.<br>
<br>
If you want give this a try, I am willing to show you.  With one wave, I guarantee you get one full blue bubble <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
