Uberbuff the warrior to collect the mobs.  When he gets back, he makes sure that they are all in a neat little pile.  Then, the clerics start chain casting superior heal on the enchanters and the one warrior (one cleric per).  The enchanters just start casting their chain stuns, perhaps even throwing in one AE Magic Debuf before the second enchanter starts chain stunning.  At this point, mezing is completely pointless, and everyone involved that doesn't have an AoE OR PBAoE spell just starts stunning or whacking just about anything they can find.  <br>
